{
  "id": "22022421522",
  "title": "[ITD] Verify ACP (VccCore) ITD",
  "description": "<br />\n<br />\n<h4>Flow *</h4>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\" id=\"isPasted\">In DMR Cores ITD, TTD are managed autonomously by Acode.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Each core (2 cores included in DCM) is fed by in-die FIVR (placed at the base), that FIVR is driven by dual VCCIN_EHV VRs.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">The ITD/TTD compensation would be done only at the FIVR Vout and is controlled by Acode.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Acode controls ITD/TTD simulatiounsly by 2 ways:</p><ol style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-left: 20px; margin: 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4;\">Periodic temperature readout adding the voltage compensation into the WP recalc.</p></li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4;\">Asynchrounious interrupt when temperature cross max allowed range (for example +-3C), using DTS DTD (Digital Thershold Detector) circuit, Non-Sticky DTD bits 0,1.</p></li></ol><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">For Acode ITD/TTD flow see&nbsp;<a href=\"https://intel.sharepoint.com/sites/big-core-IP/big_core_acode/Shared%20Documents/Forms/AllItems.aspx?RootFolder=%2Fsites%2Fbig%2Dcore%2DIP%2Fbig%5Fcore%5Facode%2FShared%20Documents%2FArch%2FAcode%20FAS%20revisions\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(65, 131, 196); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer;\">ACODE FAS (ch.4.35)</a>. The interrupt base reaction is evaluated to reduce frequency by 30-60uS.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">DCM ITD behaviour - as for the ITD interrupt based flow, any core within a DCM that will raise interrupt would trigger Acode to re-calc both cores ITD. As the 2 cores inside DCM share the same PLL, if an ITD compensation would cause a new V/F point , both cores would receive a new WP, but if only a voltage change would be done with same frequency only one core will change the voltage.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Configuration</p><ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-left: 20px; margin: 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\">Acode Fuses:<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-left: 20px; margin: 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\">Same for all CCPs</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\">uint16 FUSES_IA_ITD_CUTOFF_V2 - cutoff2 [1/C]</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\">uint16 FUSES_IA_ITD_CUTOFF_V - cutoff1 [1/C]</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\">uint8 FUSES_IA_ITD_SLOPE2 - slope goes with cutoff2</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\">uint8 FUSES_IA_ITD_SLOPE - slope goes with cutoff2</li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\">uint8 FUSES_ITD_CUTOFF_TJ - hot calibration temperature for ITD</li></ul><pre style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: inherit; margin: 15px 1em 15px 0px; font-size: 13px; white-space: pre-wrap; line-height: 19px; overflow: auto;\"><code style=\"box-sizing: border-box; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248); font-size: 14.5px; font-family: &quot;Roboto Mono&quot;, Consolas, &quot;Lucida Console&quot;, &quot;Bitstream Vera Sans Mono&quot;, monospace, sans-serif; display: inline-block; min-width: 50%; padding: 0.6em; border: 1px solid rgb(226, 226, 221); border-radius: 3px;\">Vcomp(Itd) = (slope) x (IP_V - VcutOff) x (WC temp - ITD_CutOff_Tj)</code></pre></li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\">Dedicated param for temperature&gt;Tj_max<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-left: 20px; margin: 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\">Core allowed to get a value ITD_SLOPE_ABOVE_CUTOFF_TJ to be used when temperature is highr then Tjmax (in ARL configured during Acode configuration flow via&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.intel.com/documents/pm_doc/src/MTL/HAS/Mailboxes/mailbox.html#acode-mailbox\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(65, 131, 196); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer;\">Acode mailbox</a>)</li></ul></li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\"><a href=\"https://docs.intel.com/documents/pm_doc/src/server/Wave3_common/Autonomous%20Core%20Perimeter/Autonomous%20Core%20Perimeter%20PM%20HAS.html#acp-capability-vector\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(65, 131, 196); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer;\">ACP Capability/Config message</a></li></ul><table style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1em 0px; font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); border-collapse: collapse; break-after: auto; line-height: 1.4; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><tbody style=\"box-sizing: border-box; break-inside: avoid;\"><tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\"><td align=\"right\" colspan=\"3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\"><b style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Name</b></td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\">ACP Capability msg</td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\"><td align=\"right\" colspan=\"3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\"><b style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Description</b></td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\">ACP Capability/Config message thermal related bits</td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\"><th style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: rgb(194, 223, 232); padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119);\">Bits</th><th style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: rgb(194, 223, 232); padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119);\">Access</th><th style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: rgb(194, 223, 232); padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119);\">Default</th><th style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: rgb(194, 223, 232); padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119);\">Description</th></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\"><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; text-align: center;\">6:6</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; text-align: center;\">RW</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; text-align: center;\">NA</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0.25em 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1px 0px 3px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; font-weight: bold;\">True TD enable</p>1 = ACP is allowed to apply true TD voltage correction (a.k.a inverse ITD) when a raw voltage is above ITD's minimal Vcutoff. 0 = disable. No voltage correction should be applied on a raw voltage above ITD's minimal Vcutoff. OC Driver can dynamically Disable this. As part of OC Config Repull, Acode should also pull capability vector</td></tr></tbody><tbody style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"><tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\"><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; text-align: center;\">10:10</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; text-align: center;\">RW</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; text-align: center;\">NA</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0.25em 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1px 0px 3px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; font-weight: bold;\">Advanced Thermal Control</p>1 = Acode regulates core temperature to a set temperature. Pcode does not manage per core thermals 0 = Disable advanced thermal control. Pcode manages per core thermals like legacy OC Driver can dynamically Disable this. As part of OC Config Repull, Acode should also pull capability vector</td></tr><tr style=\"box-sizing: border-box; break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\"><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; text-align: center;\">12:12</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; text-align: center;\">RW</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 2px 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto; text-align: center;\">NA</td><td style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0.25em 7px; font-size: 14.5px; border: 1px solid rgb(119, 119, 119); break-inside: avoid; break-after: auto;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1px 0px 3px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; font-weight: bold;\">ITD Throttle Enable</p>1 = Enable Throttling for ITD 0 = Disabling Throttling for ITD OC Driver can dynamically Disable this. As part of OC Config Repull, Acode should also pull capability vector.</td></tr></tbody></table><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.8em 0px 0.4em; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><a href=\"https://intel.sharepoint.com/:w:/r/sites/big-core-IP/goldencove(glc)/Shared%20Documents/HAS/PM/GLC_RWC_Acode%20algorithms%20HAS%20revisions/GLC-RWC%20Acode%20algorithms%20HAS%200.95.docx?d=w67b0a2520ea34fd5a8b5716701071cad&amp;csf=1&amp;web=1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(65, 131, 196); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer;\">GLC-RWC ACODE Algorithm HAS</a></p><ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-left: 20px; margin: 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\">Disable/Enable Fast Acode ITD/TTD - param FAST_TEMPERATURE_MANAGMENT_EN, if this would be 0 then Acode will use only the periodic TD calc and won't use the DTD to monitor +-3C diff.</li></ul><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\"><br /></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0.2em 2px 2px; padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; max-width: 60em; line-height: 1.4; padding-left: 0.5em;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Roboto, Calibri, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">1. Run function from itd.py (description of function: function picks one CCB and iterates through its cores, changing their temperature and comparing the expected voltage compensation to actual voltage compensation)</span><br /></p>\n<br />\n<h4>Configuration *</h4>\nNo particular requirements for configuration identified.<br />\n<br />\n<h4>Pass/Fail criteria *</h4>\nThe voltage offset calculated by Acode is congruent with the expected value, calculated as described in the ITD HAS.<br />\n<br />\n<h4>Intent Verification Strategy *</h4>Simics.<br />\n<br />\n<h4>HW Requirements</h4>\nN/A<br />\n<br />\n<h4>SW Requirements</h4>\nAcode, Pcode, Patch23.<br />\n<br />\n<h4>Coverage</h4>\nN/A<br />\n<br />\n<h4>Component Interactions</h4>\nN/A<br />\n<br />",
